comments: Dr. Johnson is has a generous heart. She is very helpful and lovable professor. She gives you a guideline on preparing you well on her assignments and staying on track with all of your courses. She has shown committment and dedication in her work. It was a wonderful moment and time.
Excellent professor, African and Womens history classes are not difficult, but she is a stickler for citations and class attendance.
This instructor knows research in both African American History and research in general! Really knows her stuff - but makes it easy to understand. She is very straight-forward in her teaching style.
